Business Problem: Fixing Date Formats
Problem: Order dates were imported incorrectly as strings in the confusing "YYYY/DD/MM" format. We need them as proper date objects formatted as "MM-DD-YYYY" for easier reporting.
Task: Convert the date column to the correct datetime object format and display it in the "MM-DD-YYYY" format.

df=pd.read_csv('orders_dates.csv')
df.head(10)

df['Order_Date'] = df['Order_Date'].str.strip()
df['Order_Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Order_Date'], format='%Y/%d/%m')

df

df.dtypes
df['Order_Date']=df['Order_Date'].dt.strftime('%m/%d/%Y')
df
